gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Heat 109, 76ers 104
gameRecap.excerpt: The Heat defeated the 76ers, 109-104. Bam Adebayo led the way for the Heat with 23 points, 14 rebounds and four assists, while Tyler Herro (23 points, seven rebounds, seven assists) and Duncan Robinson (20 points, 5-7 3PT FG) added a combined 43 points in the victory. Tyrese Maxey tallied 30 points, six rebounds and seven assists for the 76ers, while Buddy Hield notched 22 points (5-11 3PT FG) and 10 assists in the losing effort. The Heat have won back-to-back games as they improve to 30-25 on the season, while the 76ers fall to 32-22.
